[[File:Shiri Artstein-Avidan.jpg|thumb]] '''Shiri Artstein-Avidan''' ({{lang-he|שירי ארטשטיין-אבידן}}, born September 28, 1978) is an Israeli mathematician who in 2015 won the [[Erdős Prize]]. She specializes in [[convex geometry]] and [[Asymptotic analysis|asymptotic]] geometric analysis, and is a professor of mathematics at [[Tel Aviv University]].{{r|cv}}
==Education and career== Artstein was born in [[Jerusalem]], the daughter of mathematician Zvi Artstein. She graduated [[Latin honors|summa cum laude]] from [[Tel Aviv University]] in 2000, with a bachelor's degree in mathematics,{{r|cv}} and completed her Ph.D. at Tel Aviv University in 2004 under the supervision of [[Vitali Milman]], with a dissertation on ''Entropy Methods''.{{r|cv|mgp}} She worked from 2004 to 2006 as a Veblen Research Instructor in Mathematics at [[Princeton University]] and as a researcher at the [[Institute for Advanced Study]] before returning to Tel Aviv as a faculty member in 2006.{{r|cv}}
==Recognition== Artstein won the Haim Nessyahu Prize in Mathematics, an annual dissertation award of the Israel Mathematical Union, in 2006.{{r|hnp}} In 2008 she won the Krill Prize for Excellence in Scientific Research, from the [[Wolf Foundation]].{{r|krill}} In 2015 she won the [[Erdős Prize|Anna and Lajos Erdős Prize in Mathematics]].{{r|ep}} The award cited her "solution of Shannon's long standing problem on monotonicity of entropy (with K. Ball, F. Barthe and A. Naor), profound and unexpected development of the concept of duality, Legendre and Fourier transform from axiomatic viewpoint (with V. Milman) and discovery of an astonishing link between Mahler's conjecture in convexity theory and an isoperimetric-type inequality involving symplectic capacities (with R. Karasev and Y. Ostrover)".{{r|ep2}}
==Selected publications== With Milman and Apostolos Giannopoulos, Artstein is the co-author of the book ''Asymptotic Geometric Analysis, Part I'' ([[Mathematical Surveys and Monographs]] 202, [[American Mathematical Society]], 2015).{{r|aga}}
Her research publications include: *{{citation | last1 = Artstein | first1 = Shiri | last2 = Ball | first2 = Keith M. | author2-link = Keith Martin Ball | last3 = Barthe | first3 = Franck | author3-link = Franck Barthe | last4 = Naor | first4 = Assaf | author4-link = Assaf Naor | doi = 10.1090/S0894-0347-04-00459-X | issue = 4 | journal = [[Journal of the American Mathematical Society]] | mr = 2083473 | pages = 975–982 | title = Solution of Shannon's problem on the monotonicity of entropy | volume = 17 | year = 2004}} *{{citation | last1 = Artstein | first1 = S. | last2 = Milman | first2 = V. | author2-link = Vitali Milman | last3 = Szarek | first3 = S. J. | author3-link = Stanisław Szarek | doi = 10.4007/annals.2004.159.1313 | issue = 3 | journal = [[Annals of Mathematics]] | mr = 2113023 | pages = 1313–1328 | series = Second Series | title = Duality of metric entropy | volume = 159 | year = 2004}} *{{citation | last1 = Artstein-Avidan | first1 = S. | last2 = Klartag | first2 = B. | author2-link = Boáz Klartag | last3 = Milman | first3 = V. | author3-link = Vitali Milman | doi = 10.1112/S0025579300015497 | issue = 1–2 | journal = [[Mathematika]] | mr = 2220210 | pages = 33–48 | title = The Santaló point of a function, and a functional form of the Santaló inequality | volume = 51 | year = 2004}} *{{citation | last1 = Artstein-Avidan | first1 = Shiri | last2 = Milman | first2 = Vitali | author2-link = Vitali Milman | doi = 10.4007/annals.2009.169.661 | issue = 2 | journal = [[Annals of Mathematics]] | mr = 2480615 | pages = 661–674 | series = Second Series | title = The concept of duality in convex analysis, and the characterization of the Legendre transform | volume = 169 | year = 2009}} *{{citation | last1 = Artstein-Avidan | first1 = Shiri | last2 = Karasev | first2 = Roman | last3 = Ostrover | first3 = Yaron | doi = 10.1215/00127094-2794999 | issue = 11 | journal = [[Duke Mathematical Journal]] | mr = 3263026 | pages = 2003–2022 | title = From symplectic measurements to the Mahler conjecture | volume = 163 | year = 2014}}
